<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="157" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1698,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1698,1724]" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Total length 
<quantity box="[421,559,1698,1725]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" unit="mm" value="2.65" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.8 mm</quantity>
; body form oblong-ovate, L/W elytra 1.06–1.23 (
<figureCitation box="[1112,1221,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1042,1066]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1018]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[151,1436,181,1018]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Crostis boreas species group, dorsal and lateral aspects. 7, 8, C. boreodes, Michoacán; 9, 10, C. caperata, Chiapas. Scale bars 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809963/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">Figs. 7–8</figureCitation>
). Characteristic for this species of 
<taxonomicName box="[315,395,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Crostis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[315,395,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">Crostis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are (i) transverse pronotum with disc longitudinally striate or with striae broken into elongate punctures and most of flanks with elongate punctures (
<figureCitation box="[787,927,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–16" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-26@6.[151,1436,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11–16. Crostis boreas species group, details of pronotum. 11, 12, C. boreas, Texas; 13, 14, C. boreodes, Michoacán; 15, 16, C. caperata, Chiapas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809967" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809967/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">Figs. 13–14</figureCitation>
), (ii) length of first funicular article slightly shorter than combined lengths of articles 2–4, (iii) punctures of ventrites I and II large (
<figureCitation box="[1141,1224,1807,1833]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–19" captionStartId="7.[151,264,964,988]" captionTargetBox="[229,1359,181,941]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[229,1359,181,941]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17–19. Crostis boreas species group, ventral aspects. 17, C. boreas, prosternum with anteriorly covered fovea; 18, C. boreas, punctation on ventrites; 19, C. boreodes, punctation on ventrites. Scale bars 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809969/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
), lateralmost areas of ventrite I with 2 punctures along length, ventrites I and II with distinct isodiametric microsculpture (also on metasternum), and (iv) penis with apex protruded medially, strongly expanded laterally towards base, endophallus distally with symmetrical, elongate, fluted, gutter-like endophallite with equally thickened and sclerotized margins, apodemes 
<emphasis box="[270,304,1951,1976]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">ca.</emphasis>
2.2× longer than length of penis body (
<figureCitation box="[747,830,1951,1977]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–22" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[295,1242,1072,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-62@7.[265,1322,1049,1938]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20–22. Crostis boreas species group, male genitalia, dorsal aspect. 20, C. boreas, Texas; 21, C. boreodes, Michoacán; 22, C. caperata, Chiapas. Scale bar 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809971" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809971/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="158" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1698,2013]" box="[199,1101,1987,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1987,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is derived from the similarity of this species to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prena &amp; Anderson" authorityYear="2022" box="[986,1094,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Crostis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boreas">
<emphasis box="[986,1094,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">C. boreas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809963" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6809963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809963/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" startId="5.[151,264,1042,1066]" targetBox="[151,1436,181,1018]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1042,1102]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,329,1042,1066]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">FIGURES 7–10.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prena &amp; Anderson" authorityYear="2022" box="[337,485,1042,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Crostis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boreas">
<emphasis box="[337,485,1042,1066]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Crostis boreas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, dorsal and lateral aspects. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[922,969,1042,1066]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">7, 8,</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prena &amp; Anderson" authorityYear="2022" box="[976,1100,1042,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Crostis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boreodes">
<emphasis box="[976,1100,1042,1066]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">C. boreodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, Michoacán; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1242,1300,1042,1066]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">9, 10,</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prena &amp; Anderson" authorityYear="2022" box="[1308,1430,1042,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Crostis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caperata">
<emphasis box="[1308,1430,1042,1066]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">C. caperata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, Chiapas. Scale bars 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1148,1463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,389,1148,1174]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Natural history.</emphasis>
The three known specimens have been sifted from leaf litter in forests from 
<quantity box="[1252,1407,1148,1175]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.885" metricValueMax="3.17" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="m" value="2885.0" valueMax="3170.0" valueMin="2600.0">2600–3170 m</quantity>
in elevation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1148,1463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1220,1246]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Notes.</emphasis>
Two of the specimens are incorrectly labelled as 
<collectingRegion box="[831,943,1220,1246]" country="Mexico" name="Queretaro de Arteaga" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Querétaro</collectingRegion>
but GPS coordinates indicate the locality is just across the state border into 
<collectingRegion box="[506,634,1256,1282]" country="Mexico" name="Michoacan de Ocampo" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Michoacán</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
